The censor is an officer in the various Roman successor states who is responsible for maintaining the census supervising public morality and overseeing certain aspects of the government's finances

A consul served in the highest elected political office of the Roman Republic however after the establishment of the Empire the consuls held very little power and authority with the Emperor acting as the supreme leader
The magister officiorum is one of the most senior administrative officials in the late Roman Empire and it's successor states
